      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a great start, really hits the core of it. but for a college-level essay, I need to make sure I can preemptively shut down the opposition. like, when people try to argue for meritocracy or say it’s unfair to tax people who worked hard, how can I frame those arguments as being fundamentally flawed or even logically unsound in the context of racial equity? i want to show why their views don't really hold up against the reality of systemic issues.",
