      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The meritocracy argument fundamentally ignores the starting line fallacy, presupposing a level playing field that systemic racism has demonstrably rendered imaginary for marginalized groups. To claim fairness based solely on individual effort is to ignore how inherited wealth and institutional bias pre-determine opportunities from birth. Consequently, the objection to redistribution as \"unfair\" overlooks the vast, unacknowledged societal wealth accumulated through discriminatory practices, making their adherence to pure libertarian principles structurally complicit with inequality.",
