      "content": "wow that \"structurally complicit\" part is really powerful. i think that's exactly the kind of depth i need for the conclusion. basically, can you help me draft a final paragraph that sums everything up? i want it to end on a really strong note, maybe something that emphasizes that anything less than active redistribution isn't just \"different\" policy, but actually a way of maintaining the status quo of racial injustice. like, make it feel like the only moral conclusion to reach.",
